      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load compared using the ASME V&V 20 validation metric. FEA predictions fall within experimental uncertainty bands for 10 of 11 specimens. Mean prediction error 3.8% for stiffness, 4.2% for yield load. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to clinical risk drivers identified in the risk assessment.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary mechanical performance indicators for posterior lumbar fixation failure modes (fatigue fracture, screw pullout). Linkage to hazard analysis documented in device risk file. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario must be sufficiently similar to the intended use scenario to support extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 test configuration replicates the biomechanical loading environment of a two-level posterior lumbar fusion construct under compressive-bending. Geometric and material similarity to clinical use confirmed. Required level 3 achieved."
    }
